From: hataketsu <hunganh.dev@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] mmc: meson-mx-sdio: advertise a default OCR for SDIO WiFi

meson-mx-sdio sets no default ocr_avail and relies on a vmmc regulator
or a DT "voltage-ranges" property. An SDIO WiFi card (e.g. RTL8189ES)
on a slot with neither leaves ocr_avail == 0, so the MMC core rejects
the card with "no support for card's volts" (-EINVAL).

Honor "voltage-ranges" if present, otherwise advertise the standard
3.x V range. Card power is supplied via mmc-pwrseq, so no regulator
voltage switching is required.

Signed-off-by: hataketsu <hunganh.dev@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/mmc/host/meson-mx-sdio.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/mmc/host/meson-mx-sdio.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/host/meson-mx-sdio.c
@@ -566,6 +566,15 @@ static int meson_mx_mmc_register_clks(struct meson_mx_mmc_host *host)
 	ret = mmc_of_parse(mmc);
 	if (ret)
 		return ret;
 
+	/*
+	 * meson-mx-sdio sets no default OCR. An SDIO WiFi card (e.g. RTL8189ES)
+	 * on a slot with no vmmc regulator would leave ocr_avail == 0, and the
+	 * MMC core rejects it with "no support for card's volts". Honor a DT
+	 * "voltage-ranges" if present, else advertise the full 3.x V range;
+	 * power is supplied via mmc-pwrseq, so no regulator switching is needed.
+	 */
+	mmc_of_parse_voltage(mmc, &mmc->ocr_avail);
+	if (!mmc->ocr_avail)
+		mmc->ocr_avail = 0x00ffff00;
+
 	ret = mmc_add_host(mmc);
 	if (ret)
 		return ret;
